ChemistryLab.jl
===============

A computational chemistry toolkit for thermodynamic equilibrium
calculations.

Copyright (C) 2025-2026 Jean-François Barthélémy and Anthony Soive
                        (Cerema, UMR MCD)

Portions of this software are Julia ports adapted from the Reaktoro
C++ library (https://github.com/reaktoro/reaktoro),
Copyright (C) 2014-2024 Allan Leal, distributed under the
LGPL-2.1-or-later. The portions concerned are:

- The Helgeson-Kirkham-Flowers (HKF) standard thermodynamic model for
  aqueous solutes in `src/thermodynamics/thermo_models.jl`.
- The Haar-Gallagher-Kell / Johnson-Norton / Shock water property
  functions in `src/thermodynamics/water_properties.jl`.
- The Arrhenius rate constant and the saturation-ratio formulation
  used by the transition-state theory rate model in
  `src/kinetics/rate_models.jl`.
- The `transition_state` and `first_order_rate` rate factories
  implementing the Palandri-Kharaka / transition-state theory model
  of mineral dissolution-precipitation kinetics in
  `src/kinetics/kinetics_reactions.jl`.

The remainder of the package — including the `StateView`, `KineticFunc`,
`KineticsProblem`, `KineticsSolver` abstractions, the Parrot-Killoh
cement hydration model, the calorimetry model, the Gibbs
energy minimisation equilibrium layer, the chemical formula / species /
stoichiometric-matrix infrastructure, and the database readers — is
original work.

